# agent-device (Callstack)

Use **agent-device** for app/device automation on Hermes Mobile — not as a generic shell.

Before planning device work:

```bash
export PATH="$HOME/.npm-global/bin:$PATH"
agent-device --version
agent-device help workflow
```

If missing: `bash scripts/install-agent-device.sh` (pins `0.19.3` to match `hermes-mobile/package.json`). Do **not** run `npx -y agent-device@latest`.

## When to use what

| Tool | Use for |
|------|---------|
| **agent-device** | Exploratory QA, connection/Tailscale/fresh-user UI proofs, screenshots + a11y snapshots, RN debugging (`help react-native`) |
| **Maestro** (`npm run e2e:*`, continuous LaunchAgent) | Deterministic CI / ship-guard / chat-send-persistence; `latest.json` is the ship gate |
| **adb** / `hermes-mobile-pair.js` | Install, pair, `adb reverse`, package clear — not primary UI inspection |

Full matrix: [hermes-mobile/docs/AGENT-DEVICE.md](../../hermes-mobile/docs/AGENT-DEVICE.md).

## Hermes loop

```bash
agent-device open com.iganapolsky.hermesmobile --platform android --serial "$SERIAL" --session hermes
agent-device press 'label="Hermes"' --session hermes --settle
agent-device snapshot --session hermes
agent-device close --session hermes
```

Or: `bash hermes-mobile/scripts/agent-device-connection-proof.sh`

Prefer `open -> snapshot -i -> act -> re-snapshot -> verify -> close`. Keep mutating commands on one session serial. Chat composer automation must type only **`make money today`**.
